<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd" MadCap:conditions="Products.Analyzer,Products.Contributor,Products.Flare" MadCap:lastBlockDepth="10" MadCap:lastHeight="1366" MadCap:lastWidth="1289">
    <body>
        <MadCap:snippetBlock src="../../Banners/Contributor/z_DarkPrintBackground_SupportedInContributionNewDocWorkflows.flsnp" MadCap:conditions="Products.Contributor" />
        <MadCap:snippetBlock src="../../Banners/Flare/Feature_Supported/PDF_XHTML_XPS.flsnp" MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare" />
        <p>
            <snippetText src="../../PageLayouts/PageNumberSummary1.flsnp" />
        </p>
        <MadCap:dropDown>
            <MadCap:dropDownHead>
                <MadCap:dropDownHotspot>how to insert a page number into a frame</MadCap:dropDownHotspot>
            </MadCap:dropDownHead>
            <MadCap:dropDownBody>
                <ol>
                    <li>Open a page in a page layout.</li>
                    <li>
                        <p>Click on the frame to which you want to add a page number.</p>
                        <p class="note" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #bed230;&quot; class=&quot;mcFormatColor&quot;&gt;Note: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;">You can insert a page number only into header, footer, and decoration frames. You cannot insert a page number into a body frame (which automatically displays content from your topics).</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <MadCap:snippetText src="../../StepsGeneral/DoOneOfTheFollowingDependingOnUI.flsnp" />
                        </p>
                        <ul class="FirstLevel">
                            <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Local Toolbar</span> In the local toolbar, click <img src="../../../Images/select_frame_text_btn.png" class="ReduceButtonSize" />.</li>
                            <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Right-Click</span> Right-click the frame and select <span class="Emphasis">Select Frame Text</span>.</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>The Select Frame Text dialog opens. </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>In the <span class="Emphasis">Template Folders</span> section, select a template.</p>
                        <p class="note" MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #bed230;&quot; class=&quot;mcFormatColor&quot;&gt;Note: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;">You can click the <span class="Emphasis">Manage Templates</span> button <img src="../../../Images/manage_templates_btn.png" class="ReduceButtonSize" /> if you want to open the Template Manager. This lets you manage any of your template files (e.g., add new templates, enter descriptions for templates). <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Print">For more information see the online Help.</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.OnlineLive">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Templates/Managing_Templates.htm">Managing Templates</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
                    </li>
                    <MadCap:snippetBlock src="../../EmptyPageBreakAfter.flsnp" MadCap:conditions="FlareGuides.FlarePrintedOutputGuide,FlareGuides.FlareSnippetsGuide" />
                    <li>
                        <p>In the <span class="Emphasis">Templates</span> section, select one of the page number snippets.</p>
                        <MadCap:snippetBlock src="../../PageLayouts/PageNumberSnippetList.flsnp" />
                        <MadCap:snippetBlock src="../../PageLayouts/InsertPageNumberTip.flsnp" />
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <snippetText src="../../StepsGeneral/ClickOK.flsnp" />
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <snippetText src="../../StepsGeneral/SaveYourWork.flsnp" />
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </MadCap:dropDownBody>
        </MadCap:dropDown>
        <MadCap:dropDown MadCap:conditions="Products.FlareOnlineOnly">
            <MadCap:dropDownHead>
                <MadCap:dropDownHotspot MadCap:conditions="Products.FlareOnlineOnly">notes</MadCap:dropDownHotspot>
            </MadCap:dropDownHead>
            <MadCap:dropDownBody>
                <p class="note" MadCap:conditions="Products.FlareOnlineOnly" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #bed230;&quot; class=&quot;mcFormatColor&quot;&gt;Note: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;">In addition to inserting page numbers, you can add regular text, Heading variables, and Running Head variables into frames. See <xref href="../../../../Page_Layouts/Frames/Adding_Text_and_Content_to_Frames.htm">Adding Text and Content to Frames</xref>, <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Page_Layouts/Frames/Inserting_Heading_Variables_Into_Frames.htm">Inserting Heading Variables Into Frames</MadCap:xref>, and <xref href="../../../../Page_Layouts/Frames/Inserting_Running_Head_Variables_into_Frames.htm">Inserting Running Head Variables into Frames</xref>.</p>
                <MadCap:snippetBlock src="../../Notes/NoteIndexAutoNumbers.flsnp" MadCap:conditions="Products.FlareOnlineOnly" />
            </MadCap:dropDownBody>
        </MadCap:dropDown>
        <MadCap:dropDown MadCap:conditions="Products.FlareOnlineOnly">
            <MadCap:dropDownHead>
                <MadCap:dropDownHotspot>What's Next?</MadCap:dropDownHotspot>
            </MadCap:dropDownHead>
            <MadCap:dropDownBody class="Final">
                <p>After you insert a page number into a frame, you can specify the format of the number (e.g., decimal, lowercase Roman, uppercase alpha). You can also specify whether the numbering should begin at a certain number. Both of these tasks can be accomplished when you associate the page layout with a TOC entry. See <xref href="../../../../Output/Printed_Output/More_About_Printed_Output/Specifying_Chapter_Breaks_for_Printed_Output.htm">Specifying Chapter Breaks and Page Layouts</xref>.</p>
            </MadCap:dropDownBody>
        </MadCap:dropDown>
        <p MadCap:conditions="General.OnlineNotWebHelp">
            <conceptLink term="PageLayoutFramesSnap" />
        </p>
        <MadCap:snippetBlock src="../../EmptyPageBreakAfter.flsnp" MadCap:conditions="FlareGuides.FlarePrintedOutputGuide" />
    </body>
</html>